A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a giant frozen glacier in the shape of a corporate filing cabinet, with tiny workers in hard hats attempting to chip away at its edges using small pickaxes. The glacier sits in the middle of a warm, flowing river representing progress, causing the water to divert around it. Steam rises where the warm water meets the ice. In the background, sleek modern boats wait impatiently behind the frozen obstruction. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and icy blues, with a weathered paper texture overlay typical of mid-century business magazine covers.
